name: PhoneNumberKit 2.0.0
body: - Swift 4 support (thanks @dpopov, @irace, @SwiftRabbit ).

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.4.0
body: Metadata updates for release 8.8.1

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.3.0
body:
- Metadata updates for release 8.7.0
- PhoneNumberTextField API improvements (thanks @phatmann, @MattKiazyk)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.2.3
body:
- Metadata updates for release 8.4.0
- add isPartialFormatterEnabled check for PhoneNumberTextField (thanks @hongxinhope)
- Fix for PhoneNumberTextField edit formatting error (thanks @Jwolkovitz)
- Support semicolon as extension separator (thanks @appsforall)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.2.2
body:
- Metadata updates for release 8.0.1.
- Link CoreTelephony only on supported platforms (thanks @jshier).
- Test must not made any assumption about the current locale (thanks @Jean-Daniel).
- Adopt `Equatable` and `Hashable` by `PhoneNumber` + minor fixes (thanks @artyom-stv)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.2.1
body:
- Support for use in app extensions (thanks @vhbit)
- Fix for incorrect default region code fallback in iOS10+ (thanks for reporting @Sol88)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.2.0
body: - Fixing swift version issue for Xcode 8.2

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.1.1
body: - Metadata updates for release 8.0.0

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.1.0
body:
- Further performance improvements by removing now unnecessary locks.
- Solving bug when parsing numbers with short extensions (includes removing NSDataDetector).

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0.5
body:
- Additional performance improvements by removing .filter (thanks again @sgapr)
- Replacing NSOperation with Grand Central Dispatch.

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0.4
body: - Improvements to ignoreType and README update (thanks @sgapr)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0.3
body:
- Metadata updates for release 7.7.5
- Get leading digits method (thanks @NikKovIos)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0.2
body:
- Metadata updates for release 7.7.4
- Partial formatter bug fix by @brianmichel
- Fix crash when referencing delegate.textField() by @jrogers 
- Add ability to ignore type @sorth-hiya 
- Max concurrent queue by @cemonet

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0.1
body: - Fixes PartialFormatter access control bug (thanks @SiNBizkit)

name: PhoneNumberKit 1.0
body:
- Swift 3.0 transition.
- API redesign for improved memory management and threading.
- 'The grand renaming' of API functions.  
- Metadata updates for release 7.7.1

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.8.5
body:
- Add support for macOS, tvOS and watchOS - thanks @adamkornafeld.
- PhoneNumberTextField bug fix - thanks @Bomb3rman.
- Metadata updates (7.5.1).

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.8.4
body: - Metadata updates (7.4.2)

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.8.3
body: - Build settings update

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.8.2
body: - Metadata updates

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.8
body:
- Fix PartialFormatter for regions that are not the main country (thanks @fikus).
- Prefix optional in PhoneNumberTextField and PartialFormatter.
- Add isValidNumber computed property to PhoneNumber.
- Fix SIGABRT crash on ParseMultiple fixed. 
- Updated metadata.

name: Release 0.7
body:
- Significant improvements to type determination (thanks @fikus).
- Memory leak fixed. 
- Updated metadata.

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.6
body:
What's new:
- AsYouTypeFormatter (!) - a fully editable UITextField subclass that formats phone numbers on the fly.
- Updated metadata to latest. 

:construction: PhoneNumberKit is still beta software. :construction:

body:
What's new:

body:

name: PhoneNumberKit 0.1 alpha
body:
First release for PhoneNumberKit, a new Swift framework for working with phone numbers.
